<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06065073 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06065073 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Four San Leandro High School students have been charged with resisting arrestin connection with a violent melee last October, when police officers stoppeda black student for jaywalking. Three of the 17-year-old boys also werecharged with battery, and a fourth was charged with assault. A hearing isscheduled March 13 and 14 at Alameda County Juvenile Court in San Leandro. Theriot occurred Oct. 24 after an officer stopped the jaywalking student wholater claimed that several white students also were jaywalking, but policepicked him out of the crowd. That sparked a melee between officers fromseveral agencies and about 400 high school students. It ended with six arrestsand several injuries among students, prompting the school to cancel classesfor a day and a half.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  FOUR CHARGED IN RIOT AT SAN LEANDRO HIGH  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910305  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  135  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday March 5, 199100065073,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>